<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCoase1960">Coase, Ronald H. (1960). "The Problem of Social Cost". <i>Journal of Law and Economics</i> <b>3</b> (1): 1–44. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F466560" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F466560" rel="nofollow">10.1086/466560</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Problem+of+Social+Cost&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Law+and+Economics&amp;rft.aulast=Coase&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+H.&amp;rft.au=Coase%2C+Ronald+H.&amp;rft.date=1960&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=1%E2%80%9344&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1086%2F466560&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coase_theorem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><i>Conway v. O'Brien</i>, <a href="/wiki/Case_citation" title="Case citation">111 F.2d 611</a> (2d Cir. 1940).</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFGjerdingen1983">Gjerdingen, Donald (1983). "The Coase Theorem and the Psychology of Common-Law Thought". <i>Southern California Law Review</i> <b>56</b>: 711.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Coase+Theorem+and+the+Psychology+of+Common-Law+Thought&amp;rft.jtitle=Southern+California+Law+Review&amp;rft.aulast=Gjerdingen&amp;rft.aufirst=Donald&amp;rft.au=Gjerdingen%2C+Donald&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft.volume=56&amp;rft.pages=711&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coase_theorem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFGilles1994">Gilles, Stephen G. (1994). "The Invisible Hand Formula". <i>Virginia Law Review</i> <b>80</b> (5): 1015–1054. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F1073624" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F1073624" rel="nofollow">10.2307/1073624</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Invisible+Hand+Formula&amp;rft.jtitle=Virginia+Law+Review&amp;rft.aulast=Gilles&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen+G.&amp;rft.au=Gilles%2C+Stephen+G.&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.volume=80&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=1015%E2%80%931054&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.2307%2F1073624&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coase_theorem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHalpin2007">Halpin, Andrew (2007). "Disproving the Coase Theorem?". <i>Economics &amp; Philosophy</i> <b>23</b>: 321–341. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017%2FS0266267107001514" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017%2FS0266267107001514" rel="nofollow">10.1017/S0266267107001514</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Disproving+the+Coase+Theorem%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Economics+%26+Philosophy&amp;rft.aulast=Halpin&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rft.au=Halpin%2C+Andrew&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.pages=321%E2%80%93341&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1017%2FS0266267107001514&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coase_theorem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
